  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Two Column Layout Example</title>
  <style>
    /* Float-based two-column layout */
    .float-row {
      width: 90%;
      margin: 34px auto;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 2px solid #b0b0b0;
      padding: 0;
      background: #fcfcfc;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }
    .float-col {
      float: left;
      width: 48%;
      margin: 1%;
      min-height: 160px;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      background: #f3f5fa;
      border: 1px solid #dcdcdc;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 18px;
    }
    /* Clear floats at end */
    .float-row::after {
      content: "";
      display: table;
      clear: both;
    }

    /* Grid-based two-column layout */
    .grid-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 18px;
      width: 90%;
      margin: 34px auto;
      border: 2px solid #b0b0b0;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 18px;
    }
    .grid-col {
      min-height: 160px;
      background: #e7f9f9;
      border: 1px solid #cde4e7;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 18px;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }
    /* Basic styling */
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #f5f5fa;
    }
    h2 {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 36px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Two Column Layout: Floats</h2>
  <div class="float-row">
    <div class="float-col">
      <strong>Column 1 (Float)</strong>
      <p>This section uses the classic float technique for a two-column layout. Adjust the width as needed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="float-col">
      <strong>Column 2 (Float)</strong>
      <p>Floats require clearfix for the parent and are suitable for basic layouts or legacy browser support.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h2>Two Column Layout: CSS Grid</h2>
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="grid-col">
      <strong>Column 1 (Grid)</strong>
      <p>This section uses CSS Grid, which is powerful and modern for building two-column and complex layouts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-col">
      <strong>Column 2 (Grid)</strong>
      <p>Grid lets you control gaps and content alignment with a clean, flexible syntax.</p>
